*The targeted metabolites from KORA are classified into five analyte classes, namely glycerophospholipid (GPL), acylcarnitine (AC), sphingolipid (SL), amino acid (AA), and monosaccharide (MS). One view group comprises metabolites from the glycerophospholipid class, while the other view group comprises metabolites from the other classes.

Two mono-omics datasets and one multi-omics dataset are used as benchmark datasets to evaluate the performance of LEOPARD and established methods. The mono-omics datasets are constructed with the proteomics data from the MGH COVID study and the metabolomics from the KORA cohort, respectively. Views in both datasets correspond to panels or biochemical classes. Missingness in these datasets exemplifies a common issue encountered in longitudinal studies where data from certain panels or biochemical classes are incomplete in some but not all timepoints. The third dataset is a multi-omics dataset consisting of both metabolomics and proteomics data from the KORA cohort. In this dataset, views correspond to different omics. This dataset exemplifies the situation where data of a type of omics is incomplete. These three datasets comprise data of two views or view groups (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
